{"name": "env-isolation", "metadata": {"name": "env-isolation", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU Lesser General Public License v3 (LGPLv3)", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Internet", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": "https://github.com/aaad/env-isolation", "license": "GPL 3.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["requests"], "summary": "Isolates the environment to seperate pip environments.", "upload_time": 1735828924}, "documentation": ["# Python Library env-isolation\n\nThe `env-isolation` is a library that allows to create isolated environments for running Python code. It is useful for seperating pip environments.\n\nNote: The Library do not isolate the environments for security purposes.\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall this library in a [venv] using pip. [venv] is a tool to\ncreate isolated Python environments.\n\n### Supported Python Versions\n\nPython >= 3.6\n\n### Mac/Linux\n\n```console\npip install venv\npython -m venv <your-env>\nsource <your-env>/bin/activate\n<your-env>/bin/pip install env-isolation\n```\n\n### Windows\n\n```console\npip install venv\npython -m venv <your-env>\n<your-env>\\Scripts\\activate\n<your-env>\\Scripts\\pip.exe install env-isolation\n```\n\n## Example Usage\n\nCreate a directory `test-model` with a file `test-model/requirements.txt` with the following content:\n\n```text\npandas\n```\n\nCreate a file `test-model/main.py` with the following content:\n\n```python\nimport logging\nimport pandas as pd\n\nclass Model():\n    def __init__(self):\n        logging.info('Test Model initialised')\n\n    def execute(self, arguments: dict) -> dict:\n        logging.info(f'Test Model executed with arguments: {arguments}')\n        return pd.read_csv('test.csv').to_dict()\n```\n\nExecute the following code:\n\n```python\nimport logging\nlogging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)\nfrom envisolation import EnvIsolatedModel\n\nmodel = EnvIsolatedModel(model_id=\"test-model\", model_path=\"test_model\", pip_requirements_path=\"test_model/requirements.txt\")\nlogging.info(model.execute({\"input\": \"test\"}))\nmodel.unload()\n```\n\n[venv]: https://docs.python.org/3/library/venv.html\n"], "modules": [{"name": "envisolation.model_executor", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "envisolation.model_executor.stop_server", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "envisolation.model_executor.parser", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "envisolation.model_executor.args", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "envisolation.model_executor.model_exception", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "envisolation.model_executor.model", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "envisolation.model_executor.model_exception", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "envisolation.model_executor.SimpleHTTPRequestHandler", "bases": ["http.server.BaseHTTPRequestHandler"], "methods": [{"name": "envisolation.model_executor.SimpleHTTPRequestHandler.log_request", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "code", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "size", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Suppress logging of requests"]}, {"name": "envisolation.model_executor.SimpleHTTPRequestHandler.do_GET", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "envisolation.model_executor.SimpleHTTPRequestHandler.do_POST", "asynchro